The 48 Laws of Power by Robert Greene | Law Number 15... Crush Your Enemy Totally

2
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:13,400
All great leaders since Moses have known that

3
00:00:13,410 --> 00:00:17,289
a feared enemy must be crushed completely.
(Sometimes they have learned this the hard

4
00:00:17,289 --> 00:00:22,969
way.) If one ember is left alight, no matter
how dimly it smolders, a fire will eventually

5
00:00:22,969 --> 00:00:28,538
break out. More is lost through stopping halfway
than through total annihilation: The enemy

6
00:00:28,539 --> 00:00:33,789
will recover, and will seek revenge. Crush
him, not only in body but in spirit.

7
00:00:33,789 --> 00:00:38,509
4 Ways to Kill or be Killed
1. Do not sympathize with your enemies.

8
00:00:38,509 --> 00:00:42,979
Your enemy will bide his time and strike back
when you least expect.

9
00:00:42,979 --> 00:00:48,289
2. When you pity or hope for reconciliation,
it will make you hesitate.

10
00:00:48,289 --> 00:00:52,219
They may act friendly for the time being,
but they will eventually destroy you

11
00:00:52,219 --> 00:00:57,189
3. An enemy that is left around is like a
half-dead viper that you nurse back to health.

12
00:00:57,189 --> 00:01:00,049
You only strengthen their fear and hatred
of you.

13
00:01:00,049 --> 00:01:05,179
4. Give your enemies nothing to negotiate,
no hope, no room to maneuver.

14
00:01:05,180 --> 00:01:09,789
Do not humiliate, yet nurture these resentful
vipers who will one day kill you.

15
00:01:09,789 --> 00:01:14,060
This is all the truer with a former friend
who has become an enemy. The law governing

16
00:01:14,060 --> 00:01:19,060
fatal antagonisms reads: Reconciliation is
out of the question. You must exterminate,

17
00:01:19,060 --> 00:01:22,478
crush, and deny them the chance to return
to haunt you.

18
00:01:22,478 --> 00:01:27,228
